id: pm-v657
title: pm-governance-audit comments-audit limit contract contradicts runtime alias semantics
description: "Reconcile comments-audit pagination controls so agents can independently bound scanned items and emitted full-history rows, while preserving old spellings through an explicit compatibility policy."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:contracts","area:extensions",governance-audit,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:36:43.602Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T21:36:43.602Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "Runtime, help, package contracts, completions, and docs define one truthful pagination grammar; --limit-items remains the scanned-item cap; a canonical row-output cap bounds full-history rows without lowering scan coverage; legacy --limit behavior remains available as a documented hidden/deprecated alias or a migration hint; conflicting legacy/canonical values return a targeted structured recovery; focused tests cover independent caps and compatibility"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
severity: low
environment: Installed pm-governance-audit with pm 2026.7.13
repro_steps: Run pm comments-audit --limit-items 10000 --full-history --limit 100000 --json.
expected_result: "The documented scanned-item and output-row limits apply independently, allowing complete item coverage with a bounded row payload."
actual_result: "The command exits because --limit and --limit-items must match, revealing that runtime treats them as aliases despite help describing different scopes."
component: pm-governance-audit/comments-audit
customer_impact: "Large-workspace audits cannot independently control scan completeness and token/output size, and agents waste a retry discovering the hidden alias rule."
